8. Conclusion

We have presented a complete mathematical framework for dust mitigation on Martian PV arrays, covering electrodynamic adhesion with triboelectric charging, PINN‑based state estimation with convergence guarantees, and safe reinforcement learning control with sublinear regret and PID‑Lagrangian stability. All key components are accompanied by theorems and proofs, ensuring theoretical soundness. The architecture and design parameters are derived from first principles, enabling future numerical implementation without requiring physical experiments. This work bridges the gap between applied physics and control theory, offering a provably effective solution to a critical challenge in planetary exploration.



